@behindthescenesphotos5133 1800 screens is a limited release?  OK.  It's more than documentaries usually see by a very wide margin.  And $7.1M still works out to under $4K per screen gross.

They better be charging Pay Per View on Prime and  hoping a buttload of people pony up for it.

Of course payoffs aren't always profitable on the ledger.  They're more an act of goodwill.
